<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     03-14 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0126</SECOND>
<UNK>AP Bureau Chief Named For Oklahoma</UNK>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lindel Hutson, news editor for The Associated
Press in Indianapolis since 1980, has been named the AP's bureau
chief in Oklahoma City.
   The appointment was announced Monday by AP President Louis D.
Boccardi. Hutson succeeds Robert Shaw, who recently was named bureau
chief in Indianapolis.
   Hutson, 42, a native of Hardy, Ark., and a graduate of Arkansas
State University, joined the news cooperative in Little Rock in
1972. He transferred to the AP's General Desk in New York in 1978
and was named news editor in Indianapolis two years later.
   Hutson began his journalism career at the Jonesboro (Ark.) Sun
and also worked at the Texarkana Gazette before joining the AP.
</TEXT>
