<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--LiftDerailed     03-14 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Lift Derailed,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Aspen Chair Lift Derailed by Winds; No One Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASPEN, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 45 mph wind gust derailed the cable on a
chair lift and operators had to lower about 220 skiers to the ground
with ropes, a spokesman said.
   Most of the skiers on the Bell Mountain lift were only 20-25 feet
off the ground but some were as high as 55 feet when the cable
derailed Monday, Aspen Ski Co. spokesman Jon Reveal said.
   No injuries were reported, he said.
   ``There is an automatic system which will stop the lift if there
is a derailment. That was activated, the lift came to a halt and we
evacuated the lift,'' he said.
