<HEAD>Day-By-Day Activities Aboard Discovery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a day-by-day schedule of the
astronauts' activities aboard Discovery. All times EST:
   
   Today:
   3:57 a.m. _ Crew wakeup.
   Day is devoted to experiments, including those involving
photographs to document how man and nature are damaging Earth,
growth of chicken egg embryos in weightlessness, photographing four
rats whose legs have been cut to study the healing process in
weightlessness, growth of protein crystals and chromosome and plant
cell division.
   6:57 p.m. _ Begin eight-hour sleep period.
   
   Wednesday:
   2:57 a.m. _ Crew wakeup.
   Day of experiments.
   5:57 p.m. _ Begin eight-hour sleep period.
   
   Thursday:
   1:57 a.m. _ Crew wakeup.
   Day of experiments.
   5:57 p.m. _ Begin eight-hour sleep period.
   
   Friday:
   1:57 a.m. _ Crew wakeup.
   7:42 a.m. _ Crew will be interviewed on NBC's ``Today'' show.
   Astronauts begin shutting down experiments, stowing gear and
checking flight control systems in preparation for landing the next
day.
   5:57 p.m. _ Begin eight-hour sleep period.
   
   Saturday:
   1:57 a.m. _ Crew wakeup.
   7:27 a.m. _ Close payload bay doors.
   10:03 a.m. _ Deorbit burn.
   11:04 a.m. (8:04 a.m. PST) _ Land at Edwards AFB, Calif., after
flight of five days, one hour, seven minutes.
