<FILEID>AP-NR-03-14-89 0230EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-BarbersBrawl     03-14 0213</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Barbers Brawl,0223</SECOND>
<HEAD>Barbers Clash Over Marcos Return, One Killed</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CLARO CORTES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight barbers fought with scissors and
broken beer bottles in a drunken brawl over whether exiled President
Ferdinand Marcos should be allowed to return home, police said today.
   One barber was killed, and another was seriously wounded, they
reported.
   Police investigator Alfredo Amores said the fight took place
early Sunday, hours after the eight barbers left their shop and went
to a nearby restaurant in Manila's Malate tourist district.
   The barbers had begun arguing over Marcos' return even before
closing shop and resumed the argument over bottles of beer in the
restaurant, Amores said.
   The former president was ousted in a February 1986
civilian-military uprising that catapulted Corazon Aquino to the
presidency.
   Marcos fled to Hawaii, and Mrs. Aquino has refused to allow the
ailing Marcos to return, citing security reasons.
   Amores said tempers flared during the argument, and finally the
barbers pulled out their scissors and started stabbing each other.
   One of the barbers died of multiple stab wounds on the spot, and
another was critically wounded, Amores said.
   One was arrested and jailed, but the five others had escaped when
police arrived, Amores said. There was no word on charges.
</TEXT>
