<SECOND>PM-People-Griffith,0196</SECOND>
<HEAD>Melanie Griffith Says Alcohol Is Behind Her</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Melanie Griffith says she's had it with
alcohol. And she insists that this time she means it.
   ``Nothing works if I drink,'' the star of ``Working Girl'' said
in April's Ladies' Home Journal. ``It's a battle and you lie and you
deceive yourself and other people. All that's gone away. There's no
more of that in my life and I struggle to be honest.''
   The 31-year-old Griffith, who is pregnant and plans to remarry
``Miami Vice'' star Don Johnson, says she thinks she finally solved
her problems with drinking during rehabilitation last spring at the
Hazelden Foundation in Minnesota.
   ``It changed my life. I'm still battling the devil over here on
my shoulder, but if I go one day at a time, I can do it,'' she said.
   Now, she added, all she wants is a normal life.
   ``To be an actor you have to have a life,'' she said. ``Actors
that are just in the mirror and want to make great movies are full
of it. You have to have life experience and people experience.''
