<FIRST>d a PM-Kids-Pickups     03-14 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Kids-Pickups,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Texas Bill Would Ban Kids Under 12 From Back of Pickups</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Riding in the back of a pickup is a Texas
way of life that's got to go, a legislator says.
   A bill that would prohibit children under 12 from riding in the
back of a pickup passed the Senate in a voice vote Monday and was
sent to the House.
   Thirty people, seven under 12, were killed riding in the back of
pickups in Texas last year, said the bill's sponsor, Sen. Carl
Parker.
   ``I saw some article where it quoted somebody as saying that
riding in the back of a pickup was a Texas way of life,'' Parker
said. ``Well, I submit to you this is one area where Texas leads the
nation and, in fact, it is a Texas way of death, and it's time to
put a stop to it.''
   Parker's bill would make it a misdemeanor to carry a child in the
back of a pickup on a public road at more than 15 mph. Fines range
from $25 to $200.
</TEXT>
