<HEAD>Marauding Gunmen Kill Two</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marauding gunmen killed two men and
wounded seven other people Tuesday, police said, bringing to eight
the number killed in indiscriminate attacks in Pakistan's largest
city in six days.
   Army troops in trucks and jeeps mounted with machine guns
enforced around-the-clock curfews in several districts of Karachi
known as flashpoints for ethnic unrest.
   Police said they are uncertain what motivates the gunmen, who
fire randomly from cruising cars and motorcycles.
   Casualties have occurred among several rival ethnic groups,
according to police and hospital sources.
