here from India, have left more than 700 people dead in the past
three years in this seaport of 9 million.
   Immigrants claim discrimination in white-collar jobs keeps them
low in the labor market. Native Pakistani groups, many of them poor,
blame the immigrants for a scarcity of blue-collar jobs.
