<TEXT>
   Swarms of mosquitoes invaded the cockpit
of an Indian Airlines plane at Calcutta airport and delayed the
flight for two hours, news reports said Tuesday.
   The pilot of the Boeing 737 made the discovery when he climbed
into the cockpit shortly before departure Monday, according to
United News of India and Press Trust of India.
   Airport authorities arranged to have the cockpit cleared and the
plane took off for the eastern city of Dibrugarh, 500 miles
northeast of Calcutta.
