   Lacroix, freed on bail after his arrest last September, faces a
maximum sentence of five years.
   ``It's going to be a long road,'' said a smiling Lacroix as he
announced he would ask his lawyer to appeal the guilty verdict
reached by a jury after 2{ days' deliberation.
   Justice Jean Bienvenue of Quebec Superior Court set sentencing
for Wednesday.
   ``Only time will tell,'' replied Lacroix when asked by reporters
whether he still has a future as a television evangelist. ``It
really doesn't depend on me.''
