<TEXT>
   Coastal Corp. extended its $2.6 billion offer for
Texas Eastern Corp. outstanding stock despite Texas Eastern's
agreement to be acquired by rival suitor Panhandle Eastern Corp.
   Coastal's cash tender offer is set to expire March 31 with the
extension, the second since Texas Eastern's $3.2 billion merger
agreement with Panhandle Eastern.
   Company spokesman R.W. Wells said Monday that despite the
apparent finality of the Panhandle Eastern deal, Coastal remains
poised for a takeover with its $42-a-share offer.
