   The U.S.-Canada free trade agreement is going
so well that the countries will likely accelerate tariff reductions,
top trade officials said.
   U.S. Trade Representative Carla Hills and Canadian Trade Minister
John Crosbie said Monday they planned to begin reviewing requests to
speed up work toward eventual removal of tariffs on certain products.
</TEXT>
