unexpectedly strong employment report late last week. The Dow Jones
average of 30 industrials rose 24.11 points to a three-week high of
2,306.25.
   The dollar drifted higher against other major currencies.
   Bond prices slipped.
   Crude oil futures climbed; copper fell sharply; grain and soybean
futures posted modest gains; and frozen pork belly futures continued
drifting lower.
