<FIRST>r f BC-Belgium-InterestRates     03-14 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Belgium-Interest Rates,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Belgium Lowers Key Interest Rate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The central bank Tuesday cut the
interest rate on three-month treasury bills, Belgium's key lending
rate, to 8.4 from 8.3 percent and the one and two-month rates by
0.05 point each, to 8 and 8.2 percent respectively.
   It was the first time since last December that Belgium has
reduced its short-term interest rates.
   The move reflected a recent stabilization in international
interest rates following a steady rise since the beginning of 1989,
analysts said.
   However, the key three-month rate is still almost one point above
its level of December 1988 when it stood at 7.5 percent.
   The bank did not comment on the rate cuts. It left the interest
rate on four-month certificates unchanged at 8.4 percent but raised
that of the six-month paper to 8.4 from 8 percent.
</TEXT>
