   The stock market pulled back in mid-morning
trading today after a good opening, as institutional investors took
to the sidelines to await Wednesday's merchandise trade deficit
report.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down 0.89 point at
2,305.36 at 11 a.m. EST. The blue-chip indicator was up 3.39 points
