   Declining issues outpaced advancers by around 7 to 6 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 606 issues down, 521 up and 594 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 51.83 million shares.
   Analysts said the bond market reacted favorably to a government
report released this morning showing retail sales declined 0.4
percent in February. The bond market's enthusiasm pulled stock
prices higher.
   The lower retail numbers indicated the Federal Reserve's efforts
to slow the economy by tightening credit and raising interest rates
are working.
   ``The retail sales figures leads one to believe that inflation is
not running away,'' said John Burnett, senior vice president,
