<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet3pm     03-14 0399</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0419</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market drifted in dull afternoon
trading after seesawing through much of the session as skittish
investors awaited Wednesday's merchandise trade deficit report.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 2.32 points at
2,308.57 at 3 p.m. EST. The blue-chip indicator was up 5.71 points
an hour earlier.
   Declining issues barely outpaced advancers on the New York Stock
Exchange, with 704 issues down, 638 up and 580 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 119.6 million shares.
   The stock market tracked an early rally in the bond market
following an unexpected 0.4 percent drop in retail sales last month.
   ``The consensus was looking for flat to up 0.4 percent and that
helped relieve concern that the economy is overheating,'' said
Alfred E. Goldman, vice president for A.G. Edwards &amp; Sons Inc.
   By mid-morning, the enthusiasm fizzled and the stock market
drifted lower in the face of a weakening dollar. Investors fear a
lower dollar will lead to inflation, credit-tightening by the
Federal Reserve and surging interest rates.
   After staging a brief rally around midday, the market began
drifting with little apparent direction.
   Volume remained light with institutional investors taking to the
sidelines to await the U.S. merchandise trade deficit report for
January, analysts said. The report is scheduled to be released on
Wednesday.
   Some economists have predicted that the U.S. trade deficit for
January will narrow from $10.23 billion in December to about $9.7
billion.
   In addition, investors are awaiting reports later in the week on
housing sales, industrial production and wholesale prices to
determine whether the Federal Reserve's tight credit policy is
working.
   Last Friday's data showing unemployment fell to a 15-year low in
February sent inflationary shivers through the market as investors
reasoned that strains on the capacity of the labor force might stir
inflation and result in higher interest rates. The market bounced
back from a brief sell-off but volume has remained light.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
down 0.03 at 165.97.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index advanced
0.05 at 330.59.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, several blue-chip
stocks were down, including IBM, off } to 118[, and Ford Motor, down
| to 50{.
   Citicorp was up [ at 26|, Philip Morris advanced ] at 119[ and
Exxon was unchanged at 44~.
</TEXT>
