<FIRST>u f AM-TimesMirror-Magazine     03-14 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Times Mirror-Magazine,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Times Mirror Halts Publication of Sports inc. The Sports Business
Weekly</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Sports inc. The Sports Business Weekly is cq</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Times Mirror Co. said Tuesday it will cease
publishing Sports inc. The Sports Business Weekly, citing a lack of
advertising in the 15-month old magazine.
   The magazine debuted in January 1988 and had a controlled
circulation of 25,000. The last issue will be the March 20 issue.
   Edward E. Johnson, chairman of Times Mirror Magazines, said
Sports inc. had been widely praised by industry leaders, but he
added, ``Unfortunately, this readership enthusiasm was not matched
by advertising support.''
   Some information that has appeared in the magazine now will be
used regularly in The Sporting News, another Times Mirror
publication, the company said in a release.
   ``While we are of course disappointed with this outcome, it
certainly does not lessen our commitment to the magazine field, in
which we have grown significantly in recent years,'' the company
said.
   Times Mirror also publishes such sports-oriented magazines as
Field &amp; Stream, Outdoor Life, Golf Magazine and Ski Magazine.
