<HEAD>Chrysler Boosts Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. on Tuesday increased
cash-back incentives on some of its cars.
   The nation's No. 3 automaker boosted the $750 incentive on some
models of its Chrysler LeBaron and Dodge Daytona automobiles to
$1,000 effective immediately.
   Other cars and trucks in the program can qualify for interest
rates as low as 4.9 percent and rebates ranging from $300 to $2,000,
